  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Fleet Operations Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Role Description</strong></p><p>This is a <strong>full-time, on-site role</strong> for a <strong>Fleet Operations Executive</strong> based in Singapore. The Fleet Operations Executive is responsible for the <strong>day-to-day management and coordination of the company’s vehicle fleet</strong>, ensuring vehicles are well-maintained, operational, and deployed efficiently.</p><p>Key responsibilities include managing servicing and inspection schedules, driving vehicles for maintenance and logistics purposes, coordinating repairs and breakdown support for rental vehicles, liaising with workshops and inspection centres, and ensuring compliance with regulatory requirements. The role is hands-on and requires strong organisational skills, attention to detail, and the ability to respond to operational issues promptly.<br /></p><p><strong>Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Possess a valid <strong>Class 3 driving licence</strong> (Class 4 is welcomed)</li><li>Comfortable driving and handling different types of vehicles</li><li>Experience in <strong>fleet operations, automotive, logistics, or rental operations</strong> is an advantage</li><li>Detail-oriented with strong organisational and multitasking abilities</li><li>Able to work independently and coordinate with internal teams and external vendors</li><li>Strong interpersonal and communication skills</li><li>Basic proficiency in operational or fleet-related software tools is an advantage</li><li>Diploma in Business Administration, Logistics, Automotive, or a related discipline is preferred but <strong>not mandatory</strong></li></ul><p><strong>Additional Information:</strong></p><p><strong>Working Conditions</strong></p><ul><li>6-day work week</li><li>8 hours per day / 44 hours per week</li><li>Working hours: <strong>10:00am – 6:00pm</strong></li></ul><p><strong>Benefits</strong></p><ul><li>Competitive remuneration (based on experience)</li><li><strong>Overtime pay for breakdown or rescue jobs outside working hours (paid per trip)</strong></li><li>Stable, supportive, and hands-on work environment</li><li>Opportunity to gain practical experience in fleet and rental operations</li></ul>",
